This paper deals with natural language generation from RDF data, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The approach used in the paper involves machine learning techniques, which can be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves extracting information from RDF data and presenting it in a natural language format. Additionally, the paper deals with databases (cs.DB) as it involves processing RDF data. Finally, the paper involves language generation (cs.LG) as it deals with generating Brazilian Portuguese texts from RDF data.
